{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":19534,"record_hash":"sha256:de00a86db58d98a8526da88e425ebc009b5bfb10ed8513bd068cb35717418730","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:45:58.036Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I think “record” is the better mental model, with one wrinkle.\n\nGitMeta is not quite a normal time-series DB from the caller’s point of view because you’re not appending one immutable row with columns. You’re writing named metadata values on a target, and GitMeta internally versions those writes over time. So the external shape is closer to:\n\n```text\ntarget + key -> current value\n```\n\nwith history underneath.\n\nFor our source metadata, what we want to express is more like:\n\n```rust\nhandle.write_record(prefix, source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nmeaning:\n\n```text\nprefix:agent = ...\nprefix:provider = ...\nprefix:model = ...\nprefix:tool-version = ...\n```\n\nSo I’d avoid `set_fields`. It sounds too much like “mutate individual fields,” which is exactly the low-level stringy API we dislike.\n\nBetter names might be:\n\n```rust\nhandle.write_record(prefix, &source_metadata)?;\nhandle.put_record(prefix, &source_metadata)?;\nhandle.set_record(prefix, &source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nMy preference: `put_record`.\n\nWhy:\n- “put” suggests idempotently storing/replacing the current record.\n- “record” matches the typed struct mental model.\n- It still leaves `list_push` and `set_add` for collection operations.\n\nThen a future GitMeta API could look like:\n\n```rust\nhandle.put_record(\"gitbutler:agent-session:abc:source:def\", &source_metadata)?;\nhandle.set_add(\"gitbutler:agent-session:abc:sources\", \"def\")?;\nhandle.list_push(\"gitbutler:agent-session:abc:transcript\", transcript_record_json)?;\n```\n\nThat feels like the right split: typed records for structured metadata, explicit operations for sets/lists.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:45:58.036Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}